# Database migrations

- Migrations live in `cmd/migrations/sql/` and are applied with **Atlas** (`Makefile` targets `migrate-up`, `migrate-down`, `migrate-inspect`).
- New migration files: use the repo’s timestamp naming convention (e.g. `YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.sql`).
- After adding or changing migration SQL, refresh checksums with **`make migrate-hash`** (runs `atlas migrate hash` on `cmd/migrations/sql`) so `atlas.sum` stays in sync — do not hand-edit `atlas.sum`.
- Prefer additive, backward-compatible changes when production data exists; document breaking schema steps in the migration comment header if unavoidable.
